get.summary:
Fetch all accounts associated for the provided user, where the user has the provided permission.
Required permissions:
- read:accounts

post.summary:
Creates an account for the authenticated user.
Required permissions:
- None (authenticated only)

parameters.name: body
parameters.description: CreateAccountRequest is the request for the CreateAccount function.

put.summary:
Update an account identified by the given ID.
Required permissions:
- write:account

parameters.name: account.id
parameters.description:
Unique identifier for the account (in GUID format).
This is a read-only field and will be available after an account is created.

get.summary:
Get an account identified by the given ID.
Required permissions:
- read:account

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format).
This is a required field.

delete.summary:
Deletes an account identified by the given ID.
Required permissions:
- delete:account

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format).
This is a required field.

get.summary:
Fetch all account invites in the account identified by the given account ID.
Required permissions:
- read:invites

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) to list invites for.
This is a required field.

get.summary:
Fetch an account invite identified by the given account ID and invite ID.
Required permissions:
- read:invites

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) the invite belongs to.
This is a required field.

parameters.name: inviteId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the invite (in GUID format).
This is a required field.

delete.summary:
Delete an account invite
Required permissions:
- delete:invites

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) the invite belongs to.
This is a required field.

parameters.name: inviteId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the invite (in GUID format) to delete.
This is a required field.

post.summary:
Accept an account invite
The authenticated user's email address must match the email address specified in
the invite.
Required permissions:
- None (authenticated only)

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) the invite is for.
This is a required field.

parameters.name: inviteId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the invite (in GUID format) to accept.
This is a required field.

post.summary:
Reject an account invite
The authenticated user's email address must match the email address specified in
the invite.
Required permissions:
- None (authenticated only)

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) the invite is for.
This is a required field.

parameters.name: inviteId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the invite (in GUID format) to reject.
This is a required field.

get.summary:
Fetch all account members in the account identified by the given account ID.
The authenticated user must be a member of the account identifier by the given account ID.
Required permissions:
- read:users

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) to list members for.
This is a required field.

get.summary:
Fetch an account member by its id.
The authenticated user must be a member of the account that the member is for.
Required permissions:
- read:users

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) the member belongs to.
This is a required field.

parameters.name: userId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the user (in GUID format).
This is a required field.

delete.summary:
Delete an account member
The authenticated user must be a member of the account that the member is for.
Required permissions:
- delete:users

parameters.name: accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account (in GUID format) the member belongs to.
This is a required field.

parameters.name: userId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the user (in GUID format) to delete.
It is allowed to delete the authenticated user (aka leave account), however only if at least one other user remains in the account.
If you are the owner of the account a random other user will be automatically assigned as owner.
It is recommended to transfer ownership of the account before leaving. // TODO: how?
This is a required field.

post.summary:
Create a new account invite.
Required permissions:
- write:invites

parameters.name: accountInvite.accountId
parameters.description:
The identifier of the account this invite is for (in GUID format).
This field is required when creating an invite.

get.summary:
Fetch all account invites for the authenticated user (across all accounts).
These are the invites you are invited to join, not the ones you have sent.
Required permissions:
- None (authenticated only)

parameters.name: statusFilter
parameters.description:
Optional: Filter invites by status (e.g. pending only).

 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED: Default, unspecified status.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_PENDING: The invite is pending and waiting for the user to accept or reject.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_ACCEPTED: The invite has been accepted by the user.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_REJECTED: The invite has been rejected by the user.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_CANCELED: The invite has been canceled (e.g., by an account admin).

id.description:
Unique identifier for the invite (in GUID format).
This is a read-only field, generated by the server.

accountName.description:
Human readable name of the account that the human is invited to join.
This is a read-only value.

userEmail.description:
The email address of the user being invited.
This field is required when creating an invite.

userRoleIds.description:
The identifiers of the roles to be assigned to the user upon accepting the invite.
This field is required when creating an invite, and the list must not be empty.
Each string in the list must be a valid UUID, to be resolved in the provided account.
Please use IAMService.ListRoles to get the possible roles to assign.

createdAt.description:
The timestamp when the invite was created.
This is a read-only field.

createdByUserId.description:
The identifier of the user who created the invite (in GUID format).
This is a read-only field, populated by the server based on the authenticated user.

createdByName.description:
Name of the user that created this invite.
This is a read-only value, populated by the server based on the created_by_user_id field.

lastModifiedAt.description:
The timestamp when the invite was last updated (e.g., status change).
This is a read-only field.

userId.description:
Identifier of the user that accepted or rejected this invite.
This is a read-only value.

status.description:
The status of the invite.
This is a read-only field.

accountInvite.description:
The details of the invite to create.
This is a required field.
accountInvite.title:
The details of the invite to create.
This is a required field.

v1AccountInvite.description: An AccountInvite represents an invitation for a user to join an account.

v1AccountInviteStatus.description:
AccountInviteStatus defines the possible statuses of an account invitation.

 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED: Default, unspecified status.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_PENDING: The invite is pending and waiting for the user to accept or reject.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_ACCEPTED: The invite has been accepted by the user.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_REJECTED: The invite has been rejected by the user.
 - ACCOUNT_INVITE_STATUS_CANCELED: The invite has been canceled (e.g., by an account admin).

A User represents a user in the Qdrant cloud.
buf:lint:ignore QDRANT_CLOUD_REQUIRED_ENTITY_FIELDS

v1UserStatus.description:
UserStatus defines the possible statuses of a user account.

 - USER_STATUS_UNSPECIFIED: Default, unspecified status.
 - USER_STATUS_ACTIVE: The user account is active and can be used.
 - USER_STATUS_BLOCKED: The user account is blocked and cannot be used.
 - USER_STATUS_DELETED: The user account has been marked for deletion or is deleted.
